===Etymology===
From {{etyl|gmh|de}} {{m|gmh|echt}}, borrowed from {{etyl|gml|de}} {{m|gml|echt||lawful, genuine}}. The original form is Middle Low German {{m|gml|ēhaft||lawful}}, from {{m|gml|ē||law}} (related to modern {{m|de|Ehe}}); then {{m|gml|ēhacht}} by the Low German development ''-ft-'' → ''-cht-'' (compare {{m|de|Nichte}}); and eventually contracted into ''echt''. Cognate to {{etyl|goh|-}} {{m|goh|ēhaft||honourable}} and {{etyl|nl|-}} {{m|nl|echt}}.

